Melt butter in medium saucepan on medium heat. Add leeks; cook 5 min. or until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in garlic; cook and stir 2 min. Add asparagus, broth and water; stir. Simmer on medium-low heat 5 min. or until asparagus is crisp-tender. Season with salt and pepper. Meanwhile, mix cream cheese spread and milk until well blended. Add asparagus mixture to blender, in batches; blend until smooth. Spoon into soup bowls. Add cream cheese mixture; swirl gently with spoon.